name: treatment of used long liner, steel | used long liner, steel | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/21565/documentation

This dataset represents the end of life of steel trawlerlong liners, per 1000 kg of light ship weight, based on data from Peru (2004-3013), corresponding to 9 vessels (from a fleet of 54) for which data was available with different levels of detail. Specific data for specific inventory items may be based on sub-samples for which detailed data was available. Vessel dimensions: 34 - 275 m3 (16 - 34 m length).;System boundaries and relation between activities

Treatment of used vessel (recycling)

End of life (decommissioning). Excludes engines and motors. Excludes energy for dismantling. Excludes gear.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/03:Fishing and aquaculture/031:Fishing/0311:Marine fishing
tags: Sector: Waste Treatment & Recycling; Fishing & Aquaculture

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from Peru, extrapolated to global (GLO)
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Peru features various shipyards and relevant ship-building and ship-retrofitting expertise.

exchanges.description: EOL of a long liner, per 1000 kg of light ship weight (LSW), after 35 years lifetime. Regressions based on mainly primary data were created to relate the weight of each inventory item to a long liner's LSW. The list of inventory items (granularity) contribute >95% of environmental impacts, as described in the reference publication.
